tweet: One of the other reasons public health is a leader is because of our ability to use data for the public's good! #pophealthrt

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: Every community will have to sort through the best leadership - there's no exact recipe. For more information, check out the Practical Playbook by @deBeaumontFndtn!

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: What a great problem we have that everybody cares about public health and the social determinants right now! At the local level, it is the public health official who has the statutory responsibility to address the public's health but they cannot do it alone.

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: @Walmart also did a project in Missouri that led to a change of the local dog leash law, so community members could exercise without worry of feral dogs. This is only a tiny beginning, and this is a real opportunity for the business community!

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: There are great models of the local & national business community working with partners to address the social determinants, such as @nashhealthorg & national corporations like @generalelectric whose work in Houston caused the food bank to restructure their distribution points.

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: What I always tell trainees is you only get to be a medical student and a resident once. Focus on your medical education! Focus on clinical excellence - but do it all with the heart of public health and then you can turn your attention to the rest.

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: Yes it's a very active space. Check out @SIREN_UCSF for a great example! But, buyer beware - make sure they're using non-proprietary standards and APIs.

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: Thanks for your question! Yes there are. Particularly the housing and financial sectors. Great example to check out: @BHPNetwork

name: Karen DeSalvo
tweet: There's a lot that we can learn from LMICs who really think about health as the outcome & both public health and medicine as the inputs & in those worlds the workforce and the data are much more integrated. The hope is that they don't move in a direction of compartmentalizing.
